## ğŸ§  Settings Module (settings.py)

This is the heart of Django project configuration.

ğŸ“ Location: `myproject/settings.py`

Important settings:

ğŸ”¹ 1. INSTALLED_APPS

Apps used in project

```python
INSTALLED_APPS = [
    'django.contrib.admin',
    'django.contrib.auth',
    'django.contrib.contenttypes',
    'django.contrib.sessions',
    'django.contrib.messages',
    'django.contrib.staticfiles',
]
```
ğŸ”¹ 2. DATABASES

Default uses SQLite

```python
DATABASES = {
    'default': {
        'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.sqlite3',
        'NAME': BASE_DIR / 'db.sqlite3',
    }
}
```

ğŸ”¹ 3. TEMPLATES

Where HTML files are stored

python
'DIRS': [BASE_DIR / 'templates'],


ğŸ”¹ 4. STATIC FILES (CSS, JS, Images)

python
STATIC_URL = '/static/'


ğŸ”¹ 5. DEBUG

python
DEBUG = True   # Turn False in production


